<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="rasp-oat-bar" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Raspberry Oatmeal Bars</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup all-purpose flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup rolled oats</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup packed light brown sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon baking soda</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{8}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup butter, softened</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl. Rub in butter using a silicone spatula to form a crumbly mixture.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Line 8" x 8" square pan with greased foil. Press 2 cups oat mixture into the bottom of the pan.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Spread jam to within 1/4 inch of the edge.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top; press down lightly into jam.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Bake at <m>350^\circ</m> for 35-40 minutes. Let it cool before cutting into bars.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>